<item>
            <title>[LU-9812] Source rpm does not cleanly build with --rebuild</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9812</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Doing &lt;tt&gt;rpmbuild --rebuild lustre-2.10.0-1.src.rpm&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
results in the following issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;+ ln -s Lustre.ha_v2 /home/build/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/lustre-2.10.50-1.x86_64/etc/ha.d/resource.d/Lustre
ln: failed to create symbolic link &apos;/home/build/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/lustre-2.10.50-1.x86_64/etc/ha.d/resource.d/Lustre&apos;: No such file or directory
error: Bad exit status from /var/tmp/rpm-tmp.HpX1JT (%install)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Doing &lt;tt&gt;make rpms&lt;/tt&gt; from within source works, but the user should be able to rebuild rpms from source.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
